The paper proposes a mathematical model for the channel from the input DNA sequence to the observed current in a nanopore sequencer, and calculates bounds on the information extraction capacity. This involves incorporating impairments like inter-symbol interference, deletions, and random response. This work involves information theory, signal processing, and statistical modeling, which suggests that cs.IT is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with DNA sequencing, which suggests that cs.BIO is another likely sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to sub-categories like cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), and cs.NEUR (neural and evolutionary computing) due to the algorithmic and optimization aspects of the work.
